a\";s:2975:\"<div class=\"snap_preview\"><br /><p>Finally, at last, <a href=\"http://wordpress.org/development/2008/12/coltrane/\">it&#8217;s here</a>.Â  And now, on to 2.8.Â  There were several areas that we didn&#8217;t have time to re-design for 2.7.Â  2.8 will focus on making the media and widgets UI as good as the rest of WP.Â  There will be a few new features as well.Â  Theme browsing and one-click theme install is a likely one.Â  After a short rest to recover from 2.7, we&#8217;ll start brainstorming new features and put the results on the<a href=\"http://codex.wordpress.org/Version_2.8\"> 2.8 codex page</a>.</p>\n<p>We&#8217;ll likely do the usual .1 release in a month to address any bugs that slipped through the 2.7 beta testing cycle.</p>\n<p>A lot of people contributed to 2.7, but I&#8217;d like to give a few thank yous in particular.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://iammattthomas.com/\"> </a><a href=\"http://jane.wordpress.com/\">Jane</a> for the UX, the wire frames, and for all of the help with managing this release.Â  <a href=\"http://iammattthomas.com/\">Matt</a> for the great visual design.Â  <a href=\"http://dd32.id.au/\">DD32</a> for the upgrade and install work, file system abstraction, and all of the bug fixing.Â  <a href=\"http://www.santosj.name/\">Jacob</a> for the HTTP API and all of that phpdoc.Â  <a href=\"http://www.aaronharp.com/\">Aaron</a> for quick edit. <a href=\"http://www.ilfilosofo.com/\">Austin</a> for the many bug fixes and for getting the flash uploader working with Flash 10. <a href=\"http://blogwaffe.com/\">Mike</a> for the dashboard. <a href=\"http://blog.ftwr.co.uk/\">Peter</a>, <a href=\"http://markjaquith.com/\">Mark</a>, and <a href=\"http://azaozz.wordpress.com/\">Andrew</a> for being kick ass lead devs who put in a lot of thought, love,Â  and hours.Â  And <a href=\"http://ma.tt/\">Matt</a> for bringing all of these great people together.</p>\n  <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gocomments/ryan.wordpress.com/1638/\"><img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" src=\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/comments/ryan.wordpress.com/1638/\" /></a> <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/godelicious/ryan.wordpress.com/1638/\"><img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" src=\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/delicious/ryan.wordpress.com/1638/\" /></a> <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gostumble/ryan.wordpress.com/1638/\"><img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" src=\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/stumble/ryan.wordpress.com/1638/\" /></a> <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/godigg/ryan.wordpress.com/1638/\"><img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" src=\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/digg/ryan.wordpress.com/1638/\" /></a> <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/goreddit/ryan.wordpress.com/1638/\"><img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" src=\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/reddit/ryan.wordpress.com/1638/\" /></a> <img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" src=\"http://stats.wordpress.com/b.gif?host=ryan.boren.me&blog=78&post=1638&subd=ryan&ref=&feed=1\" /></div>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Wed, 21 Oct 2009 19:30:22 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"Ryan\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:19;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:2:{s:0:\"\";a:5:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:28:\"Ryan: Hear that 2.7 a Comin\'\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:23:\"http:/